### ✅ Smell-Free Pattern (positive example)

**`ValidateOrder_NullOrder_ThrowsArgumentNullException`** (line 157) is clean:
- Single responsibility, clear naming
- Uses `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` correctly
- Asserts on a specific property (`ParamName`)
- No magic numbers, no branching, no external dependencies

